CM_ BO_ 274 "Multi-subframe (64B, 4 subframes) steering sensor on body bus. Carries BRAKE_PRESSED (byte 7 bit 1), TURN_SIGNAL_LEFT, longitudinal accel, redundant 12-bit steering angle. Right turn signal is on 0x58B (R5 splits L/R across buses).";
CM_ BO_ 308 "Byte 16 = CRC-8 (poly 0x1D, XOR 0xEB, body = bytes[17:24]); tail-positioned rather than at byte 4 like every other message in this DBC. Byte 17 high nibble is COUNTER; low nibble is LKA_ACTIVE. Observed raw states are 0, 3, 4, 6, 7, and 8; only 0x6 carried non-zero TORQUE_CMD in the 2026-04-26 stock-drive captures.";
CM_ BO_ 1205 "ADAS_ENGAGED is a multi-state enum; 0 is observed off and multiple non-zero states are observed in driving/assist contexts. Exact per-state semantics are not fully decoded yet.";

CM_ SG_ 1018 CRUISE_SET_SPEED "Cluster's cruise setpoint display source. 16-bit BE at bytes 10-11, scale 0.125 km/h. Raw 1600 (=200 km/h) is the UNSET sentinel when cruise has no target.";


VAL_ 303 GEAR_STATE 1 "R" 2 "N" 3 "B" 8 "D" ;
VAL_ 308 LKA_ACTIVE 0 "STATE_0" 3 "STATE_3" 4 "STATE_4" 6 "STATE_6" 7 "STATE_7" 8 "STATE_8" ;
VAL_ 427 LKAS_STATE 1 "ACTIVE_OR_READY" 2 "SUPPRESSED_BY_DRIVER" 3 "UNAVAILABLE" ;
